title.narrative: Strengthened and more effective child protection legislation, policies and budget are integrated across sectors.

description.narrative: Enhanced child protection legislation and policies were integrated across relevant sectors including social protection, social welfare, health, education to prevent and respond to child separation, violence, abuse and exploitation, and harmful practices surpassing the target for the year. Greater political will among policymakers and civil societies led to the harmonization of the Criminal Act, family and FGM/C laws in line with the 2010 Child Act and Convention on the Rights of the Child (CRC) and its optional protocols. Progressive allocation of resources for staffing of the social welfare and justice for children systems was ensured. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
